NEW CLASS ALERT ‼️
30 MIN HIIT CLIMB 🔥🔥

Starting next week, join me tuesdays + thursdays at 7am for our all new high intensity interval training 30 minute climb!

instead of climbing to the beat of the music we will focus on producing big + powerful moments of intensity followed by low intensity recovery periods. no choreography/combos just muscle + hustle baby! don’t worry, we’ll still be sweating to dope playlists and creating high energy in the studio. you’re going to love this new format + walk out feeling even more confident on your CLMBR. 

i’m turning 35 this year and i’m inspired to make this my strongest year yet! i started climbing a year ago this month and i am addicted to the movement, the intensity, but most importantly how i feel on and off my clmbr. 

i am so grateful to have this opportunity to share this experience with you at @studio_clmbr_la and shout out to my at home @clmbr_official familia! 

i cannot wait to explore new levels of strength, endurance and fearlessness with my #CLMBRcommunity ❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥

GUIDE TAKEOVER W/ DALIA

Dalia will be taking over our story tomorrow to give us an inside look to her day — what a treat! 😍 Follow along and say hi!

Dalia is a certified personal trainer with 13+ years of experience in the fitness industry. Whether you’re climbing at home, in a commercial gym or at the LA studio, Dalia will help you find your limits with her upbeat, fiery music and commitment to challenging you wherever you are at in your fitness journey.

WHAT MOTIVATES YOU?
I’m always so motivated and inspired by my community. Everyone has different stories, backgrounds, cultures and when these experiences come together, limitless magic happens. I learn from my team every time I teach and I apply these lessons daily as I continue to grow into the strongest leader I can possibly be. We’re in this beautiful struggle of life together.

WHAT IS YOUR VIBE AS A GUIDE?
Musica y energia is everything! I want my class to feel the music as if the beat was running through their veins. I strive to create a space for my CLMBRs to feel safe to explore new levels of strength. I want my CLMBRs to feel empowered to fail and get back up only to reach higher. Life is too short to move through it afraid to fail. I want my CLMBRs to leave class on a confidence high, ready to move through life a little more fearless.

OUTSIDE OF CLMBR, WHAT DO YOU ENJOY?
Food. Family. Friends. One of my favorite things about growing up in a Mexican household is that we were always celebrating something. Delicious food was always being made and the more friends and family to join the fun, the better! I never take for granted the opportunity to be surrounded by the people that bring me so much joy.

this may take serveral posts to say + show everything i want to share because simply the last year was one of my best ❤️‍🩹

we were notified last sunday morning that our studio would be closing after classes monday night because of reasons beyond our control. we’re all so heartbroken and honestly still in shock that this chapter has come to an end but while my whole being is hurting, i feel so lucky to have had the time with you 

the last year we collected the most amazing moments with the most incredible humans. we had no idea what to expect introducing CLMBR to west hollywood, but i knew with the passion + talent my team and i were ready to bring, it was going to be something epic. well let me tell you that epic doesn’t even begin to describe what we created. it’s too incredible to try to put the transformations, the celebrations, the prs, the hustle, the FAMILY into words - but if you were there you know. 🫶🏼

thank you, thank you, thank you, 
thank you for trusting me and my incredible team 
thank you for loving + celebrating each other 
thank you for sharing your stories 
thank you for spreading the word + bringing your friends + family to experience the magic 
thank you for being you 

thank you for everything 
 
my fellow coaches, studio consultants, and #CLMBRcommunity - it’s because of YOU this journey has been unforgettable 

i know we’re not done reaching for greatness together. not even close. we’re family now 🫶🏼. see you soon, amores. 

i love you always 

your guide,
dalia

#mexicanindependenceday #latina #latinxheritagemonth #soulcycle

Representation matters, and that’s especially true in fitness. I started teaching indoor cycling almost 8 years ago and when I looked around the fitness world, I noticed a gap – a lack of spaces where Latinas could come together, support one another, and enjoy a fun and challenging workout. 

Fast forward to four years ago when I joined @soulcycle, and it became abundantly clear to me that filling this void was a mission I was deeply committed to. My goal was to create a class that not only acknowledges but enthusiastically celebrates our distinctive culture, life experiences, our inherent strengths, and, of course, our MUSICA!

My classes are for EVERYONE, and it’s time to break the stereotypes that may have held some Latinas back from trying it out. In my class, we prove that strength and resilience come in all shapes, sizes, and backgrounds.

But it’s more than just a fitness class, it’s about cultivating a familia. We rally behind one another, exchange our stories, and foster an unwaveringly supportive community where every Latina can experience a sense of belonging, no matter her fitness level.

See you in class Hermosas! 💃🏻🫶🏼💖

MY 3 RULES FOR MY @soulcycle CLASS⭐️

1. LOVE 💖
we show up as a team. celebrate each other, celebrate yourself, and love on your people hard. walk in with an open heart and be kind to each other. 

2. ENERGIA! 💃🏻
sing. dance. find freedom to be YOU. 
there’s not a lot of moments in our day where we can wild out in a dark room, sweat away our fears, and celebrate this extraordinary life. ride loud and proud baby. 

3. CONNECT 🫶🏼
this beautiful community is the best part about what i do. be present. see each other. feel each other. smiles go a long way. if you’re new to my class please come up and say hi if i don’t get a chance to first. this familia is forever.

im approaching 5 years at Soulcycle and my goal from the start was to make my room a place where latinos feel seen and free to be EVERYTHING that we are. fitness spaces haven’t always been the most inclusive. i totally understand why showing up to a new class or gym can be intimidating. you question whether you belong, and if you’re good enough or look the right way. i have felt all of the above. 🙅🏻‍♀️

im so passionate about helping people find joy in movement. no matter what level, i want to show you how you can love yourself through your journey. i strive to make classes enjoyable but challenging mixed with a whole lot of perreo. ‘cause you know, reggaeton is LIFE. 💃🏻

in our @soulcycle casa 
we welcome everyone
we celebrate our wins 
we ride and dance through our lows

juntos, we are unstoppable 💪🏼

A big goal of mine this year is to be more consistent with my mobility training. I created this yummy mobility session for our TIU Refresh & Recharge Challenge so we can jump on this together! 

Why Mobility?! 
Think of mobility as your body’s backstage pass to flexibility, strength, and overall sexy ninja-like moves. It’s not just about touching your toes (although, that’s cool too), but it’s about owning every inch of your body’s range of motion. Whether you’re a gym warrior, dance floor perreo queen🙋🏻‍♀️, or just a human trying to adult, mobility is your BFF. 

Hermosas!! This is why were staying consistent this year and FOREVER:
FLEXIBILTY UPGRADE: Say adiós to stiffness and helllloooo to fluid movements.
INJURY PREVENTION: Dodging injuries like a superhero? That’s what happens when your joints are well-oiled machines.
POSTURE PERFECTION: Stand tall, strut proud – mobility training has your back (literally).

Tone It Up Team! I see a few of you have already completed your session! Keep the check ins coming and let me know which mobility move was your favorite! 

It’s never too late to sign up for our TIU Challenge! Click the link in my bio for more info🫶🏼
